class="hub-content-container"><div id="replace-view" ng-non-bindable><meta ng-non-bindable name="meta:slug" content="introduction"><meta ng-non-bindable name="meta:type" content="docs"><meta ng-non-bindable name="meta:parent"><meta ng-non-bindable name="meta:image" content=""><meta ng-non-bindable name="meta:title" content="Introduction"><meta ng-non-bindable name="meta:title_raw" content="Introduction"><meta ng-non-bindable name="meta:description" content="UiPath Activities are part of the UiPath Studio application and are designed to help you create a clear and smooth automation process. An activity can be defined as a piece of a puzzle. You need multiple activities, connected between them, to create the entire puzzle represented by the workflow. The..."><meta ng-non-bindable name="meta:_id" content="5d5cf458fe803c006f3999b5"><meta ng-non-bindable name="meta:hidden"><div ng-if="!suggestedEdits.isEnabled" class="templateBlock--docs"><header id="content-head"><div class="row clearfix"><div class="col-xs-9"><h1>Introduction</h1><div class="excerpt"></div></div><div class="col-xs-3"><a ng-click="suggestedEdits.enable()" href="" ng-cloak class="suggestEdits"><i class="icon icon-register"></i>Suggest Edits</a></div></div></header><div id="content-container" class="grid-container-fluid"><section class="content-body grid-75 grid-100"><div style="margin-left: 31px" ng-non-bindable class="markdown-body"><p><strong>UiPath Activities</strong> are part of the <strong>UiPath Studio</strong> application and are designed to help you create a clear and smooth automation process.</p>
<p>An activity can be defined as a piece of a puzzle. You need multiple activities, connected between them, to create the entire puzzle represented by the workflow. The complexity of activities varies from simply defining a variable to configuring them by using custom wizards. </p>
<p>All activities are integrated into packages that cover certain areas of interest. For example, activities related to manipulating <code class="rdmd-code lang-" data-lang="" name=""><button class="rdmd-code-copy fa"></button>.xlsx</code> or <code class="rdmd-code lang-" data-lang="" name=""><button class="rdmd-code-copy fa"></button>.csv</code> files are organized under the <strong>UiPath.Excel.Activities</strong> package, making it easier for you to navigate through the list of available packages.</p>
<p>You can manage your activities packages by using the feeds available at the application level or the project level. More details about the Activity Feeds and how to handle them are available <strong><a href="https://docs.uipath.com/studio/docs/managing-activities-packages#section-about-activity-feeds" target="" title="">here</a></strong>.</p>
<p>The following table lists the activities packages available by default in UiPath Studio as dependencies for all newly created projects. depending on the profile.</p>

<p>More additional packages can be added by using the <strong>Manage Packages</strong> button directly from <strong>UiPath Studio</strong>. The process of adding new packages and updating the existing ones is explained <strong><a href="/activities/docs/about-activities-packages" target="" title="" class="doc-link" data-sidebar="about-activities-packages">here</a></strong>.</p>
<p>The activities packages have a lifecycle strongly connected with the two annual Enterprise Releases and the monthly Community Releases. You can check the activities lifecycle <strong><a href="https://www.uipath.com/product-lifecycle" target="" title="">here</a></strong> for a better understanding of our updating and upgrading system and also of the support timeframe for each release.</p>
<p>We recommend to always upgrade the activities packages to the latest versions so you can enjoy them at their full capabilities. <strong><a href="https://docs.uipath.com/releasenotes/docs/uipath-system-activities" target="" title="">Release Notes</a></strong> are available for all activities packages and you can check them at any time. Even more, you can subscribe to our newsletter and receive all news directly in your email box!</p>
<p>You can choose to install the activities packages only on your local machine, you can use the official feed, or you can add dependency packages to the ones already installed.</p>
<ul>
<li><strong>Local feed</strong> means that all packages with this feature are stored on your computer.</li>
<li><strong>Official feed</strong> represents all packages that can be added to a specific project you create in UiPath Studio. You can customize each of your projects with the needed package and version.</li>
<li>A <strong>dependency package</strong> represents a set of options that can be added to an already installed package. For example, you can choose to add extra languages to a certain project, requiring you to install the UiPath.Bundle.Extended package.</li>
<li>A <strong>default process dependency</strong> represents the packages available for all project templates in <strong>UiPath Studio</strong> after initial installation.</li>
</ul>
<p>The tables below present all the available <strong>UiPath</strong> packages.</p>
<p>Default Packages available on Official and Local Feed:</p>
































































































<div class="rdmd-table"><div class="rdmd-table-inner"><table><thead><tr><th style="text-align:left"><p>Activity Package</p></th><th style="text-align:left"><p>Official Feed</p></th><th style="text-align:left"><p>Local Feed</p></th><th style="text-align:left"><p>Dependency Package</p></th><th style="text-align:left"><p>Default Process Dependency</p></th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td style="text-align:left"><p><strong>UiPath.Excel.Activities</strong></p></td><td style="text-align:left"><p><span class="img" role="button" tabindex="0"><img src="https://documentationpicturerepo.blob.core.windows.net/screenshots/screenshots/Orchestrator_2016.2/check_mark.png" alt="Image" align="" caption="" height="auto" title="" width="auto"/><span autofocus="" class="lightbox" role="dialog" tabindex="0"><span class="lightbox-inner"><img type="application/json" data-json="&quot;**UiPath Activities** are part of the **UiPath Studio** application and are designed to help you create a clear and smooth automation process.\n\nAn activity can be defined as a piece of a puzzle. You need multiple activities, connected between them, to create the entire puzzle represented by the workflow. The complexity of activities varies from simply defining a variable to configuring them by using custom wizards. \n\nAll activities are integrated into packages that cover certain areas of interest. For example, activities related to manipulating `.xlsx` or `.csv` files are organized under the **UiPath.Excel.Activities** package, making it easier for you to navigate through the list of available packages.\n\nYou can manage your activities packages by using the feeds available at the application level or the project level. More details about the Activity Feeds and how to handle them are available **[here](https://docs.uipath.com/studio/docs/managing-activities-packages#section-about-activity-feeds)**.\n\nThe following table lists the activities packages available by default in UiPath Studio as dependencies for all newly created projects. depending on the profile.\n[block:parameters]\n{\n  \&quot;data\&quot;: {\n    \&quot;h-0\&quot;: \&quot;Activities Package\&quot;,\n    \&quot;h-1\&quot;: \&quot;Default Dependency in Studio\&quot;,\n    \&quot;h-2\&quot;: \&quot;Default Dependency in StudioX\&quot;,\n    \&quot;0-0\&quot;: \&quot;**[UiPath.Excel.Activities](doc:about-the-excel-activities-pack)**\&quot;,\n    \&quot;1-0\&quot;: \&quot;**[UiPath.Mail.Activities](doc:about-the-mail-activities-pack)**\&quot;,\n    \&quot;2-0\&quot;: \&quot;**[UiPath.System.Activities](doc:about-the-system-activities-pack)**\&quot;,\n    \&quot;3-0\&quot;: \&quot;**[UiPath.UIAutomation.Activities](doc:about-the-ui-automation-activities-pack)**\&quot;,\n    \&quot;4-0\&quot;: \&quot;**[UiPath.Presentations.Activities](doc:about-the-presentations-activities-pack)**\&quot;,\n    \&quot;5-0\&quot;: \&quot;**[UiPath.Word.Activities](doc:about-the-word-activities-pack)**\&quot;,\n    \&quot;6-0\&quot;: \&quot;**[UiPath.ComplexScenarios.Activities](about-complex-scenarios-pack)**\&quot;,\n    \&quot;0-1\&quot;: \&quot;![Image](https://documentationpicturerepo.blob.core.windows.net/screenshots/screenshots/Orchestrator_2016.2/check_mark.png)\&quot;,\n    \&quot;0-2\&quot;: \&quot;![Image](https://documentationpicturerepo.blob.core.windows.net/screenshots/screenshots/Orchestrator_2016.2/check_mark.png)\&quot;,\n    \&quot;4-1\&quot;: \&quot;![no_right](https://documentationpicturerepo.blob.core.windows.net/screenshots/screenshots/Orchestrator_2016.2/no_right.png)\&quot;,\n    \&quot;5-1\&quot;: \&quot;![no_right](https://documentationpicturerepo.blob.core.windows.net/screenshots/screenshots/Orchestrator_2016.2/no_right.png)\&quot;,\n    \&quot;6-1\&quot;: \&quot;![no_right](https://documentationpicturerepo.blob.core.windows.net/screenshots/screenshots/Orchestrator_2016.2/no_right.png)\&quot;\n  },\n  \&quot;cols\&quot;: 3,\n  \&quot;rows\&quot;: 7\n}\n[/block]\n\nMore additional packages can be added by using the **Manage Packages** button directly from **UiPath Studio**. The process of adding new packages and updating the existing ones is explained **[here](doc:about-activities-packages)**.\n\nThe activities packages have a lifecycle strongly connected with the two annual Enterprise Releases and the monthly Community Releases. You can check the activities lifecycle **[here](https://www.uipath.com/product-lifecycle)** for a better understanding of our updating and upgrading system and also of the support timeframe for each release.\n\nWe recommend to always upgrade the activities packages to the latest versions so you can enjoy them at their full capabilities. **[Release Notes](https://docs.uipath.com/releasenotes/docs/uipath-system-activities)** are available for all activities packages and you can check them at any time. Even more, you can subscribe to our newsletter and receive all news directly in your email box!\n\nYou can choose to install the activities packages only on your local machine, you can use the official feed, or you can add dependency packages to the ones already installed.\n   * **Local feed** means that all packages with this feature are stored on your computer.\n   * **Official feed** represents all packages that can be added to a specific project you create in UiPath Studio. You can customize each of your projects with the needed package and version.\n   * A **dependency package** represents a set of options that can be added to an already installed package. For example, you can choose to add extra languages to a certain project, requiring you to install the UiPath.Bundle.Extended package.\n   * A **default process dependency** represents the packages available for all project templates in **UiPath Studio** after initial installation.\n\nThe tables below present all the available **UiPath** packages.\n\nDefault Packages available on Official and <script>if (navigator.appName == 'Microsoft Internet Explorer' || (window.navigator.userAgent.indexOf("Edge") > -1) || !!(navigator.userAgent.match(/Trident/) || navigator.userAgent.match(/rv:11/)) || (typeof $.browser !== "undefined" && $.browser.msie == 1))

<script>
  // no sidebar option
  if (window.location.hash.includes("nosidebar") || window.location.search.includes("nosidebar")) {
    // remove hub-sidebar-parent
    $("#hub-sidebar-parent").remove();

    // remove hub-content margin, width=100%, max-width=none
    $("#hub-content").css("margin", 0);
    $("#hub-content").css("width", "100%");
    $("#hub-content").css("max-width", "100%");
  }
	$("#hub-container").css("visibility", "visible");

  // Tabbed Content
  $(function () {
    // click tab handler
    $(document).on("click", ".tablinks", function () {
      var initialClickedEl = $(this);
      var tabLinks = $(this).parent().parent().find(".tablinks");
      var tabContents = $(this).parent().parent().find(".tabcontent");

      for (var i = 0; i < tabLinks.length; i++) {
        if ($(tabLinks[i]).text() == initialClickedEl.text()) {
          $(tabLinks[i]).addClass("active");
          $(tabContents[i]).show();
        } else {
          $(tabLinks[i]).removeClass("active");
          $(tabContents[i]).hide();
        }
      }
    });

    // Activities links
    if (
      window.location.hash.includes("studiox") ||
      window.location.search.includes("studiox")
    ) {
      $("#tab_studiox").addClass("active");
    } else {
      $("#tab_studio").addClass("active");
    }
    // Set first tab as active if another is not found
    function setInitialActiveTab() {
      $(".tab").each(function () {
        var tabLinks = $(this).find(".tablinks");
        var found = false;
        for (var i = 0; i < tabLinks.length; i++) {
          if ($(tabLinks[i]).hasClass("active")) {
            found = true;
            break;
          }
        }
        if (!found) {
          $(tabLinks[0]).addClass("active");
        }
        $(this).find(".active").click();
      });
    }

		setInitialActiveTab();
    $(window).on('pageLoad', setInitialActiveTab);

    // Content Under Drop-Down

    $(document).on("click", ".UiPathCollapsibleButton", function () {
      $(this).toggleClass("active");

      var active = $(this).hasClass("active");
      $(this)
        .parent()
        .find(".UiPathCollapsibleContent")
        .each(function () {
          if (active) {
            $(this).css("maxHeight", this.scrollHeight + "px");
          } else {
            $(this).css("maxHeight", "0px");
          }
        });
    });
  });



// Copy button for API 

  $('.js-CodeSnippet-copySnippetButton').on('click', function() {
    var copyText = $(this).parent(".js-CodeSnippet-responseResponse").find('span');

    $(this).addClass('is-clicked');

    var range = document.createRange();
    range.selectNodeContents(copyText[0]);
    var sel = window.getSelection();
    sel.removeAllRanges();
    sel.addRange(range);
    document.execCommand('copy');

    setTimeout(function() {
      copyText.parent().find('.js-CodeSnippet-copySnippetButton').removeClass('is-clicked');
      console.log('sup');
      console.log(copyText)
   	
    },1500);
	  return false;
  });
</script>

<script>
	var d = document.querySelector('meta[name="meta:hidden"]').outerHTML;
  if (d.includes('content=""')) {
    var oldText = document.title; 
    document.title = "[unpublished] " + oldText;
  }
	$(document).ready(function(){
    var d = document.querySelector('meta[name="meta:hidden"]').outerHTML;
    if (d.includes('content=""')) {
      var oldText = document.querySelector('title[ng-bind="pageTitle"]').text; 
      document.querySelector('title[ng-bind="pageTitle"]').text = "[unpublished] " + oldText;
    }
	});
</script>

<script>

  // GSE Search plmenentation
  var cseLOC = window.location.href;
  cseLOC = cseLOC.replace(/:\/\/[^/]+\//, '://docs.uipath.com/');
  // cseLOC = cseLOC.replace(/\-staging/, '');
  cseLOC = cseLOC.replace(/\/docs\/.*$/, '/docs/');
  cseLOC = cseLOC.replace(/\/reference\/.*$/, '/reference/');
  var cseCX = '004170392867827773460:uucyrrcsozz';
  var cseLR = '';

  if (cseLOC.match(/:\/\/docs.uipath.com\/$/) || cseLOC.match(/:\/\/docs.uipath.com\/[^\/]+\/docs/) || cseLOC.match(/:\/\/docs.uipath.com\/[^\/]+\/reference/) || cseLOC.match(/:\/\/docs.uipath.com\/[^\/]+\/?$/)) {
    // english, latest
    cseCX = '004170392867827773460:vkuuxuehyf4';
    //cseLOC = '&siteSearch=https://docs.uipath.com/*/docs';
    cseLOC = '&excludeTerms=lang-'
  } else {
    cseLOC = cseLOC.replace(/\.com\/[^\/]+\//, '.com/*/');
    cseLOC = cseLOC.replace(/\.com\/[^\/]+$/, '.com/*/');

    cseLOC = cseLOC.replace(/(\/lang-\w+)$/, '$1/');
    if (!cseLOC.match(/\/lang-\w+\//)) {
      cseLR = '&lr=lang_en';
    } else {
      // add slash at the end if not there
      // add /docs/ at the end if missing
      //if (cseLOC.match(/\/lang-\w+\/$/)) {
      //    cseLOC += 'docs/';
      //}
    }
    cseLOC = cseLOC.replace(/\/docs\/?$/, '');
    cseLOC = cseLOC.replace(/\/reference\/?$/, '');

    cseLOC = '&siteSearch=' + cseLOC;
  }

	console.log(cseLR);

  var cseURL = 'https://www.googleapis.com/customsearch/v1/siterestrict?key=AIzaSyC5l1wSBpRr9kMB5n2clsJ6N0QwOwiq8no&cx='+cseCX+cseLOC+cseLR;

  // var div = '<div class="gcse-search" data-as_sitesearch="' + cseLOC + '" ' + lr + '></div>';
  // document.write(div);

  console.log(cseLOC + cseLR);

  if (!$('.icons #search-div').length) {
   $('<div class="gcse-search" id="search-div"><form id="search-form" method="get"><input id="search-new-box" type="text" name="q" value="" placeholder="Search for..."><input type="submit" value="Search"><div class="search-figure"></div></form></div>')
   .insertAfter('#header-icon-nav .icons .hub-subheader-breadcrumbs');
  }

  if (!$('#SearchResults').length) {
    $('<div class="SearchResults" id="SearchResults"><div class="SearchResults-modalWrapper"><div class="SearchResults-modal"><button class="SearchResults-modalCloseButton js-SearchResults-modalCloseButton"></button></div></div></div>')
    .insertBefore('#hub-container .hub-container');
  }

  $("#search-form").submit(function(e) {

    $(':submit').attr('disabled', 'disabled');

    setTimeout(function() {
      $(':submit').removeAttr('disabled');
    }, 750)

    if ($('.SearchResults-list').length) {
      $('.SearchResults-list').remove();
    }

    if ($('.SearchResults-noResultsWindow').length) {
      $('.SearchResults-noResultsWindow').remove();
    }

    $('.SearchResults').addClass('is-active');
    $('body').addClass('no-scroll');

    e.preventDefault(e);

    var form = $(this);
    var url = cseURL;

    console.log(url);

    var theJSONobj;

    $.ajax({
      type: "GET",
      url: url,
      data: form.serialize(),
      error: function() {
        $('.SearchResults-modal').html('<div class="SearchResults-noResultsWindow"><p>An error has occurred on submit</p></div>');
      },
      success: function(data) {

        function nextPage(dataNew) {

          if (dataNew && dataNew.queries.nextPage) {
            console.log('next page exists from dataNew');
            $('.js-SearchResults-nextPageButton').removeClass('is-disabled is-hidden');
            var newIndex = dataNew.queries.nextPage[0].startIndex;

            if (!$('.SearchResults-nextPageButton').length) {
              $('.SearchResults-modal').append('<button class="SearchResults-nextPageButton js-SearchResults-nextPageButton">Next</button>');
            }

            var url = cseURL + '&start='+newIndex;

            if (newIndex > 100) {
              $('.js-SearchResults-nextPageButton').addClass('is-disabled');
            }

            $('.js-SearchResults-nextPageButton').on('click', function(event) {

                $('.js-SearchResults-nextPageButton').addClass('is-disabledVisually');

                setTimeout(function() {
                  $('.js-SearchResults-nextPageButton').removeClass('is-disabledVisually');
                }, 750)

                $('.js-SearchResults-nextPageButton').off('click');
                $('.js-SearchResults-prevPageButton').off('click');

                event.preventDefault();

                var ul = $('ul.SearchResults-list');
                ul.find('li').remove();

                if (formAJax) {
                  formAJax.abort();
                }

                var formAJax = $.ajax({
                  type: "GET",
                  url: url,
                  data: form.serialize(),
                  success: function(dataNewPage) {

                    if (typeof(dataNewPage) == 'object') {

                      if (!dataNewPage.queries.nextPage) {
                        $('.js-SearchResults-nextPageButton').addClass('is-disabled');
                      } else {
                        newIndex = dataNewPage.queries.nextPage[0].startIndex;
                        console.log('Form Submitted - New Index from dataNew = '+newIndex+'')
                      }

                      for (var i in dataNewPage.items) {
                        var itemTitle     = dataNewPage.items[i].htmlTitle;
                        var itemSiteName  = dataNewPage.items[i].pagemap.metatags[0]['og:site_name'];
                        var itemLink      = dataNewPage.items[i].link.replace(/\?.*/g,'');
                        var itemSnippet   = dataNewPage.items[i].htmlSnippet;

                        var htmlItemTitle = itemTitle;

                        if (itemSiteName != undefined) {
                          console.log(itemSiteName);
                          ul.append(
                            $('<li>').attr('style','--animation-order: '+i+';').append(
                              $('<a href="'+data.items[i].link+'" class="SearchResults-itemLink SearchResults-itemLink-1">')
                                .append($('<span class="SearchResults-title">').html(htmlItemTitle))
                                .append($('<span class="SearchResults-site">').html(itemSiteName))
                                .append($('<span class="SearchResults-link">').html(itemLink))
                                .append($('<span class="SearchResults-desc">').html(itemSnippet))
                            )
                          );
                        } else {
                          ul.append(
                            $('<li>').attr('style','--animation-order: '+i+';').append(
                              $('<a href="'+data.items[i].link+'" class="SearchResults-itemLink SearchResults-itemLink-1">')
                                .append($('<span class="SearchResults-title">').html(htmlItemTitle))
                                .append($('<span class="SearchResults-link">').html(itemLink))
                                .append($('<span class="SearchResults-desc">').html(itemSnippet))
                            )
                          );
                        }
                      }
                      nextPage(dataNewPage);
                      prevPage(dataNewPage);
                      setTimeout( function() {
                        $('.SearchResults-list').find('li').addClass('is-active');
                      }, 50);
                      return ul;

                      var lots_of_stuff_already_done = false;

                      $('.SearchResults-itemLink-1').on('click', function() {

                        if (lots_of_stuff_already_done) {
                           lots_of_stuff_already_done = false; // reset flag

                           console.log('bubbling');
                           return; // let the event bubble away
                        }

                        e.preventDefault();

                        if ($('.SearchResults').hasClass('is-active')) {
                          $('#search-new-box').val('');
                          $('.SearchResults').removeClass('is-active');
                          $('body').removeClass('no-scroll');
                        }

                        $(this).trigger('click');
                      });
                    } else {
                      var noResults = $('<div class="SearchResults-noResultsWindow"><h3>We&#39;re sorry!</h3><p class="SearchResults-noResultsQuery">No results found for "<b>'+data.queries.request[0].searchTerms+'</b>".</p><h4>Search Tips</h4><ul class="SearchResults-noResultsTips"><li>Check your spelling.</li><li>Broaden your search by using fewer or more general words.</li></ul><h4>Browse by Guide</h4><ul class="SearchResults-browse"><li><a href="https://docs.uipath.com/activities">Activities</a></li><li><a href="https://docs.uipath.com/releasenotes">Release Notes</a></li><li><a href="https://docs.uipath.com/studio">Studio</a></li><li><a href="https://docs.uipath.com/cloudplatform">Cloud Platform</a></li><li><a href="https://docs.uipath.com/studiox">StudioX</a></li><li><a href="https://docs.uipath.com/explorer-expert">Explorer Expert</a></li><li><a href="https://docs.uipath.com/robot">Robot</a></li><li><a href="https://docs.uipath.com/connect-enterprise">Connect Enterprise</a></li><li><a href="https://docs.uipath.com/orchestrator">Orchestrator</a></li><li><a href="https://docs.uipath.com/integrations">Integrations</a></li></ul><a class="SearchResults-noResultsGoogle" href="https://www.google.com/?q='+data.queries.request[0].searchTerms+'" target="_blank">Search for <b>"'+data.queries.request[0].searchTerms+'"</b> on Google!</a></div>');

        function prevPage(dataNew) {

          if (dataNew && dataNew.queries.previousPage && dataNew.queries.previousPage[0].startIndex) {

            var newIndex = dataNew.queries.previousPage[0].startIndex;
            $('.js-SearchResults-prevPageButton').removeClass('is-disabled');
            console.log('Previous Page Exists! New Index from dataNew prevPage() = '+newIndex+'')

            if (!$('.SearchResults-prevPageButton').length) {
              $('.SearchResults-modal').append('<button class="SearchResults-prevPageButton js-SearchResults-prevPageButton">Previous</button>');
            }

            var url = cseURL + '&start='+newIndex;

            $('.js-SearchResults-prevPageButton').on('click', function(event) {

                $('.js-SearchResults-prevPageButton').addClass('is-disabledVisually');

                setTimeout(function() {
                  $('.js-SearchResults-prevPageButton').removeClass('is-disabledVisually');
                }, 750)

              $('.js-SearchResults-prevPageButton').off('click');
              $('.js-SearchResults-nextPageButton').off('click');

           console.log('previous page does NOT exist');
           $('.js-SearchResults-prevPageButton').addClass('is-disabled');

        function tree(data) {
    if (typeof (data) == 'object' && data.items && data.items.length > 0) {
        var ul = $('<ul>');
        ul.addClass('SearchResults-list');
        if (data.queries && data.queries.nextPage && data.queries.nextPage.length > 0) {
            var newIndex = data.queries.nextPage[0].startIndex;
        }
        console.log('New Index = ' + newIndex + '')
        for (var i in data.items) {
            // var itemTitle     = data.items[i].pagemap.metatags[0]['og:title'];
            var itemTitle = data.items[i].htmlTitle ? data.items[i].htmlTitle : '';
            var itemSiteName = data.items[i].pagemap && data.items[i].pagemap.metatags && data.items[i].pagemap.metatags.length > 0 ? data.items[i].pagemap.metatags[0]['og:site_name'] : undefined;
            var itemLink = data.items[i].link ? data.items[i].link.replace(/\?.*/g,'') : '';
            var itemSnippet = data.items[i].htmlSnippet ? data.items[i].htmlSnippet : '';
            var htmlItemTitle = itemTitle;
            if (itemSiteName != undefined) {
                console.log(itemSiteName);
                ul.append($('<li>').attr('style', '--animation-order: ' + i + ';').append($('<a href="' + data.items[i].link + '" class="SearchResults-itemLink">').append($('<span class="SearchResults-title">').html(htmlItemTitle)).append($('<span class="SearchResults-site">').html(itemSiteName)).append($('<span class="SearchResults-link">').html(itemLink)).append($('<span class="SearchResults-desc">').html(itemSnippet))));
            } else {
                ul.append($('<li>').attr('style', '--animation-order: ' + i + ';').append($('<a href="' + data.items[i].link + '" class="SearchResults-itemLink">').append($('<span class="SearchResults-title">').html(htmlItemTitle)).append($('<span class="SearchResults-link">').html(itemLink)).append($('<span class="SearchResults-desc">').html(itemSnippet))));
            }
        }
        nextPage();
        prevPage();
        setTimeout(function () {
            $('.SearchResults-list').find('li').addClass('is-active');
        }, 50);
        return ul;
    } else {
        var noResults = $('<div class="SearchResults-noResultsWindow"><h3>We&#39;re sorry!</h3><p class="SearchResults-noResultsQuery">No results found for "<b>' + data.queries.request[0].searchTerms + '</b>".</p><h4>Search Tips</h4><ul class="SearchResults-noResultsTips"><li>Check your spelling.</li><li>Broaden your search by using fewer or more general words.</li></ul><h4>Browse by Guide</h4><ul class="SearchResults-browse"><li><a href="https://docs.uipath.com/activities">Activities</a></li><li><a href="https://docs.uipath.com/releasenotes">Release Notes</a></li><li><a href="https://docs.uipath.com/studio">Studio</a></li><li><a href="https://docs.uipath.com/cloudplatform">Cloud Platform</a></li><li><a href="https://docs.uipath.com/studiox">StudioX</a></li><li><a href="https://docs.uipath.com/task-capture">Task Capture</a></li><li><a href="https://docs.uipath.com/robot">Robot</a></li><li><a href="https://docs.uipath.com/connect-enterprise">Connect Enterprise</a></li><li><a href="https://docs.uipath.com/orchestrator">Orchestrator</a></li><li><a href="https://docs.uipath.com/marketplace">Marketplace</a></li></ul><a class="SearchResults-noResultsGoogle" href="https://www.google.com/?q=' + data.queries.request[0].searchTerms + '" target="_blank">Search for <b>"' + data.queries.request[0].searchTerms + '"</b> on Google!</a></div>');
        $('.js-SearchResults-prevPageButton').addClass('is-hidden');
        $('.js-SearchResults-nextPageButton').addClass('is-hidden');
        return noResults;
    }
}
		
		
		

        $('#SearchResults .SearchResults-modal').prepend(tree(data));

        var lots_of_stuff_already_done = false;

        $('.SearchResults-itemLink').on('click', function() {

          if (lots_of_stuff_already_done) {
             lots_of_stuff_already_done = false; // reset flag

             console.log('bubbling');
             return; // let the event bubble away
          }

          e.preventDefault();

          if ($('.SearchResults').hasClass('is-active')) {
            $('#search-new-box').val('');
            $('.SearchResults').removeClass('is-active');
            $('body').removeClass('no-scroll');
          }

          // do lots of stuff

          lots_of_stuff_already_done = true; // set flag
          $(this).trigger('click');
        });
      }
    });

  });

  // Exit modal on close Button click
  $('.js-SearchResults-modalCloseButton').on('click', function() {
    if ($('.SearchResults').hasClass('is-active')) {
      $('#search-new-box').val('');
    }

    $('.SearchResults').removeClass('is-active');
    $('body').removeClass('no-scroll');
  });

  // Exit modal on ESC press
  $(document).keyup(function(e) {
    if (e.key === "Escape") {
      if ($('.SearchResults').hasClass('is-active')) {
        $('#search-new-box').val('');
      }

      $('.SearchResults').removeClass('is-active');
      $('body').removeClass('no-scroll');
    }
  });

</script>



<script>
  // SUBSCRIBE FAB
  
var isMobile = /Android|webOS|iPhone|iPad|iPod|BlackBerry|IEMobile|Opera Mini/i.test(navigator.userAgent);
var element = document.getElementById('text');

if (isMobile){
	$(".popout .subfabbtn").click(function() {
		window.location = "https://start.uipath.com/release-Notes-2.html";
	});
}
else {
	$(".popout .subfabbtn").click(function() {
		$(this).toggleClass("subfabactive");
		$(this).closest(".popout").find(".subfabpanel").toggleClass("subfabactive");
	});
	$(document).click(function() {
		$(".popout .subfabpanel").removeClass("subfabactive");
		$(".popout .subfabbtn").removeClass("subfabactive");
	});
	$(".popout .subfabpanel").click(function(event) {
		event.stopPropagation();
	});
	$(".popout .subfabbtn").click(function(event) {
		event.stopPropagation();
	});
};

</script>



<script type="text/javascript">//<![CDATA[
	//VERSION NEXT TO HEADER-LOGO
  function copyVersion() {
  	var firstDivContent = document.querySelectorAll('.hub-breadcrumb-item')[2];
		var secondDivContent = document.getElementById('dataversion');
		secondDivContent.innerHTML = firstDivContent.innerHTML.replace( /fa fa-chevron-down/g,'');
  	if (secondDivContent.innerHTML.indexOf("v20") == "-1" ){
      secondDivContent.innerHTML = "";
    }
	}
	//Call copyVersion on body="onload"
	copyVersion();
	
	//move under header-logo
	function versionPosition() {
		$("#dataversion").detach().appendTo("#header-nav-left");
	}
	versionPosition();
	//]]>
</script>
